content:
#
# This is a Shiny web application. You can run the application by clicking
# the 'Run App' button above.
#
# Find out more about building applications with Shiny here:
#
#    https://shiny.posit.co/
#

library(shiny)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(leaflet)
library(sf)
library(plotly)


load('for_shiny_app')
load('geo')

for_shiny_app = for_shiny_app |>
  mutate(X2 = replace_na(X2, 'unknown'),X3 = replace_na(X3, 'unknown')) |>
  mutate(X2 = ifelse(X2 == 'nobilisdives', 'nobilis', X2))

mycolors = c('#FF410DFF', '#6EE2FFFF', '#F7C530FF', '#95CC5EFF')

mynamedcolors = c('castrensis' = '#FF410DFF', 'falconensis' = '#6EE2FFFF', 'liliensis' ='#F7C530FF', 'porcensis' =  '#95CC5EFF')

factpal <- colorFactor(mycolors, for_shiny_app$inst_name)


# Define UI for application that draws a histogram
ui <- fluidPage(

    # Application title
    titlePanel("STUDIUM"),

    # Sidebar with a slider input for number of bins 




        # Show a plot of the generated distribution
        mainPanel(
          tags$div(checkboxGroupInput('inst', 'Pedagogy', 
                                      inline = TRUE, 
                                      selected = unique(for_shiny_app$inst_name), 
                                      choices = unique(for_shiny_app$inst_name)),  style="display:inline-block"),
          tags$div(selectInput('wealth', 'Wealth category: ', multiple = TRUE,
                               selected = unique(for_shiny_app$X2), 
                               choices = unique(for_shiny_app$X2)),  style="display:inline-block"),
          tags$div(selectInput('age', 'Age category: ', multiple = TRUE,
                               selected = unique(for_shiny_app$X3), 
                               choices = unique(for_shiny_app$X3)),  style="display:inline-block"),
           leafletOutput("map"),
          sliderInput('years', 'Years', min = 1426, max = 1800, value = c(1426, 1800),width = '100%'),
           plotlyOutput('timeline', height = 300) )
    )


# Define server logic required to draw a histogram
server <- function(input, output, session) {

  
  map_df = reactive({

    
   d =  for_shiny_app %>%
      filter(year > input$years[1] & year < input$years[2]) %>%
      filter(inst_name %in% input$inst & X2 %in% input$wealth & X3 %in% input$age) |>
      group_by(place_id, inst_name) %>%
      summarise(n = n()) |>
      left_join(geo, by = 'place_id') |> 
      st_as_sf()
   
     d
     
     print(d)
    
  })
  
  
  output$map <- renderLeaflet({

     leaflet() |>
      clearShapes()|>
      clearControls()|> 
      clearMarkers() |>
      addProviderTiles("Esri.WorldGrayCanvas") |>
      setView(lat = 50, lng = 0, zoom = 4)
    
  })
  
  observe({
    
    leafletProxy("map", data =map_df() ) |>
      clearShapes()|> 
      clearMarkers()|>
      clearControls() |>
      addCircleMarkers(radius = ~sqrt(n), 
                       fill = TRUE, 
                       fillColor = ~factpal(inst_name), 
                       color = 'black', 
                       stroke = TRUE, 
                       fillOpacity = .75, 
                       weight = .5,
                       label = ~place_name) %>%
      addLegend(pal = factpal, values = ~inst_name, opacity = 1)
  })
  
  
  filtered_data <- reactive({
    
    for_shiny_app %>%
      filter(year >= input$years[1] & year <= input$years[2]) %>%
      filter(inst_name %in% input$inst & X2 %in% input$wealth & X3 %in% input$age) %>%
      group_by(inst_name, year, X2) %>%
      summarise(n = n())
  })
  
  output$timeline <- renderPlotly({

    
   p =  filtered_data() |>
      ggplot(aes(x = year, y = n, fill = inst_name)) + 
      geom_col(alpha = .9) + scale_fill_manual(values = mynamedcolors) + 
      theme_minimal() + 
     theme(panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(), 
           panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(), 
           legend.position = 'none', strip.background = element_rect(fill = 'gray90', size = .1)) + 
     labs(x = NULL, y = NULL) + facet_wrap(vars(X2), ncol = 2)
   
   ggplotly(p)
    
  })
  
}

# Run the application 
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
